        "Details": "The Bowman started off production as a defensive artillery platform with a pair of Arrow IVs, however, general Clan dislike of indirect fire combat, and the lack of direct combat options on the original design resulted in several redesigns. Another of the direct fire designed variants, this one mounts a HAG 20 in the right arm, and and ATM 9 in the left torso to replace the LRM-20. Four ER Medium Lasers give it decent support for when the bins run dry.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
